To compile, type the following,                                                                                                    
    gcc -o SIM -O2 simulator.c parson.c -lfftw3 -lm                                                                                

You need fftw installed to compile this. The "parson" files                                                                        
are for parsing the config files.                                                                                                  



To compile MPI version, type the following,                                                                                        
    mpicc -o MPI-SIM -O2 simulator_mpi.c parson.c -lfftw3_mpi -lfftw3 -lm                                                          

To run,                                                                                                                            
    mpirun -n <# of processes> ./MPI-SIM <config-file>                                                                             

You need fftw installed with mpi to compile this.                                                                                  
The "parson" files are for parsing the config files.




sinfo -l (list availble partitions and such)
salloc -N (# of nodes) -p (partition name)
squeue
srun (use like mpirun, -n defaults to number of nodes allocated)
    srun - N 2 --mpi=mpi2 ./SIM
use euler partition on skein, no GPUs though
module load openmpi/1.8.3-slurm
need fftw_mpi

mpicc -o MPI-SIM -O2 simulator_mpi.c parson.c -L../../local_installs/lib -I../../local_installs/include -lfftw3_mpi -lfftw3 -lm


Use gcc -fopenmp when compiling OpenMP stuff
export OMP_NUM_THREADS=8
gcc -fopenmp -o OMP-SIM -O2 simulator_omp.c parson.c -lm
